The paper deals with pseudorandomness for Boolean functions computed by read-once, depth-D circuits with unbounded fan-in over the de Morgan basis. This falls under the category of circuit complexity (cs.CC). The paper also makes use of Fourier analytic techniques for pseudorandomness, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of growth bounds for circuits, which could place it in the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
